  <h2 style='color: white; font-family: Optima'>How can we prevent CO2 levels from increasing further? </h2>
<p style='color: white; font-family: Optima'>While we cannot completely stop the rise of CO2 levels, we can stop it from increasing as quickly.<br>Here are some tips to help you do your part in reducing CO2 emissions:</p>
<ul style='color: white; font-family: Optima'>
  <li>Try reusing or recycling more instead of throwing the item away. When compressed, trash can release lots of greehouse gases into the atmosphere.</li>
  <li>Walk, bike, carpool or take public transportation whenever possible. It is a small step to reducing your carbon footprint.</li>
  <li>Use more renewable resources instead of relying on fossil fuels all the time</li>
  <li>If the world slowly started to use more renewable resources, conserve trees and forests, and reduce the amount of fossil fuels burned, the state of climate change will improve immensely.</li>
</ul>
  
